The paper discusses the optimization of SPARQL queries, which are used to query RDF data stored in relational databases. This falls under the category of database management systems (cs.DB). The paper also proposes a heuristic-based approach for query plan generation and a mechanism for detecting cardinality estimation errors at runtime, which involves artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning techniques. The paper also deals with the Join-intensive characteristic of SPARQL queries, which is related to data structures and algorithms (cs.DS). The paper also discusses the efficiency of query evaluation, which is related to information retrieval (cs.IR) and optimization (cs.LG).
